Rosalynn Carter, the former First Lady of the United States, is remembered for her dedication to various causes. She was an advocate for equal rights for women and girls, mental health and wellness, and caregivers of children, aging loved ones, and people with disabilities. She shared a deep love with her husband, former President Jimmy Carter, and their partnership exemplified humility and patriotism. Throughout their friendship, Rosalynn Carter's hope, warmth, and optimism were always felt. The nation expresses gratitude and love to the Carter family and all those whose lives were positively impacted by Rosalynn Carter.